what’s a good backup chip for laptop
I wouldn’t dip it in ranch but it’s a chip
so pretty much any big ole external drive will do.  something with twice or more the space on your laptop will pretty well never come close to running out
western digital and seagate have both worked for me
if you want to travel with it get a "portable" one so you don't have to plug it in to the wall
I only want something that can hold something like 365 22 minute videos
I want to store the ones I got downloaded before I reset the laptop
do you know what size one of those videos is?
they’re not all 22, and really that’s an extreme - most are 15-20, one or two are 30
the 100 some odd I have now is 8.64 gbish
that's smaller than I was thinking
yeah, the 22 per is overkill so I can maybe store other things like pictures too
and make sure there’s more than enough rather than too short
if 100 of the videos is less than 9 gb you don't really need a really big drive
250 gb which is pretty affordable ought to be way more than enough
I have some 5 gb drives that have the documents and pictures but like anything more than a handful of the videos said it was too much
so I may get ANOTHER drive instead of a chip but it’s the sizing I need to know
